<dl id="n12063h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12063h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12063h"> 63(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Columbanus (black) / conv Merlin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; trois hommes vraiment saints cherchent Merlin pour le convertir &hellip; Le premier arrive d&apos;Irlande; il est mont&eacute; sur un cheval noir, son manteau est noir, sa chevelure est noir, sa figure est noir, toute sa personne est noire. Merlin reconnait le grand docteur de l&apos;&eacute;glise irlandaise, Colomban <br><font color="green">[t&hellip; hree truly holy men come to convert Merlin [&hellip;]</font> The first comes from Ireland. He is seated on a black horse, his coat is black, his hair is black, his face is black and he is black all over. Merlin recognised Colombanus, the great doctor of the Irish church ] <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 66-67</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
